See https://github.com/orlp/dev-on-windows/wiki/Installing-GCC--&-MSYS2

gcc: Msys2 doesn't add the windows path, so use the full path:w
$ /C/msys64/mingw64/bin/gcc.exe --version

Setting on msys2 on windows:

$ pacman -Sy
$ pacman --needed -S bash pacman pacman-mirrors msys2-runtime
-Close and reopen msys2 
$ pacman -Su
-Close and reopen msys2 
$ pacman -S base-devel git mercurial cvs wget p7zip
$ pacman -S perl ruby python3 mingw-w64-i686-toolchain mingw-w64-x86_64-toolchain
$ pacman -S --needed base-devel mingw-w64-i686-toolchain mingw-w64-x86_64-toolchain \
                   git subversion mercurial \
                   mingw-w64-i686-cmake mingw-w64-x86_64-cmake

				   
-Now, to use gcc include the full path:
$ /C/msys64/mingw64/bin/gcc.exe
				   
-> Solution: Actually, open the mingw64.exe instead of msys2.exe to get gcc!

-Also, be sure to install ssh (see https://www.booleanworld.com/get-unix-linux-environment-windows-msys2/):

$ pacman -S openssh				   
$ ssh-keygen -f /etc/ssh/ssh_host_rsa_key -N '' -t rsa
$ ssh-keygen -f /etc/ssh/ssh_host_dsa_key -N '' -t dsa
$ ssh-keygen -f /etc/ssh/ssh_host_ecdsa_key -N '' -t ecdsa
$ ssh-keygen -f /etc/ssh/ssh_host_ed25519_key -N '' -t ed25519				   

-> In one command:

$ ssh-keygen -f /etc/ssh/ssh_host_rsa_key -N '' -t rsa && ssh-keygen -f /etc/ssh/ssh_host_dsa_key -N '' -t dsa && ssh-keygen -f /etc/ssh/ssh_host_ecdsa_key -N '' -t ecdsa && ssh-keygen -f /etc/ssh/ssh_host_ed25519_key -N '' -t ed25519	

Install emacs (see https://emacs.stackexchange.com/questions/23837/msys2-emacs-install-not-working and https://www.gnu.org/software/emacs/download.html):

$ pacman -S mingw-w64-x86_64-emacs mingw-w64-x86_64-qt5 mingw-w64-x86_64-giflib mingw-w64-x86_64-libjpeg-turbo mingw-w64-x86_64-libpng mingw-w64-x86_64-librsvg mingw-w64-x86_64-libtiff mingw-w64-x86_64-imagemagick mingw-w64-x86_64-libxml2 

OR:

$ pacman -S mingw-w64-x86_64-emacs

